90std::unique_ptr<WebGL2RenderingContext> WebGL2RenderingContext::create(CanvasBase& canvas, GraphicsContextGLAttributes attributes)
91{
92 auto renderingContext = std::unique_ptr<WebGL2RenderingContext>(new WebGL2RenderingContext(canvas, attributes));
93 // This context is pending policy resolution, so don't call initializeNewContext on it yet.
94
95 InspectorInstrumentation::didCreateCanvasRenderingContext(*renderingContext);
96
97 return renderingContext;
98}
99
100std::unique_ptr<WebGL2RenderingContext> WebGL2RenderingContext::create(CanvasBase& canvas, Ref<GraphicsContextGL>&& context, GraphicsContextGLAttributes attributes)
101{
102 auto renderingContext = std::unique_ptr<WebGL2RenderingContext>(new WebGL2RenderingContext(canvas, WTFMove(context), attributes));
103 // This is virtual and can't be called in the constructor.
104 renderingContext->initializeNewContext();
105
106 InspectorInstrumentation::didCreateCanvasRenderingContext(*renderingContext);
107
108 return renderingContext;
109}

116WebGL2RenderingContext::WebGL2RenderingContext(CanvasBase& canvas, Ref<GraphicsContextGL>&& context, GraphicsContextGLAttributes attributes)

118{

123WebGL2RenderingContext::~WebGL2RenderingContext()
124{
125 // Remove all references to WebGLObjects so if they are the last reference
126 // they will be freed before the last context is removed from the context group.
127 m_readFramebufferBinding = nullptr;
128 m_boundTransformFeedback = nullptr;
129 m_boundTransformFeedbackBuffer = nullptr;
130 m_boundUniformBuffer = nullptr;
131 m_boundIndexedUniformBuffers.clear();
132 m_activeQueries.clear();
133}
134
135void WebGL2RenderingContext::initializeNewContext()
136{
137 // FIXME: NEEDS_PORT
138 ASSERT(!isContextLost());
139
140 m_readFramebufferBinding = nullptr;
141
142 m_boundCopyReadBuffer = nullptr;
143 m_boundCopyWriteBuffer = nullptr;
144 m_boundPixelPackBuffer = nullptr;
145 m_boundPixelUnpackBuffer = nullptr;
146 m_boundTransformFeedbackBuffer = nullptr;
147 m_boundUniformBuffer = nullptr;
148
149 // NEEDS_PORT: boolean occlusion query, transform feedback primitives written query, elapsed query
150
151 m_maxTransformFeedbackSeparateAttribs = getUnsignedIntParameter(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_SEPARATE_ATTRIBS);
152 ASSERT(m_maxTransformFeedbackSeparateAttribs >= 4);
153
154 m_defaultTransformFeedback = createTransformFeedback();
155 m_context->bindTransformFeedback(GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK, m_defaultTransformFeedback->object());
156 m_boundTransformFeedback = m_defaultTransformFeedback;
157
158 m_boundIndexedUniformBuffers.resize(getIntParameter(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_UNIFORM_BUFFER_BINDINGS));
159 m_uniformBufferOffsetAlignment = getIntParameter(GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER_OFFSET_ALIGNMENT);
160
161 m_packRowLength = 0;
162 m_packSkipPixels = 0;
163 m_packSkipRows = 0;
164 m_unpackRowLength = 0;
165 m_unpackImageHeight = 0;
166 m_unpackSkipPixels = 0;
167 m_unpackSkipRows = 0;
168 m_unpackSkipImages = 0;
169
170 m_max3DTextureSize = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_3D_TEXTURE_SIZE);
171 m_max3DTextureLevel = WebGLTexture::computeLevelCount(m_max3DTextureSize, m_max3DTextureSize);
172 m_maxArrayTextureLayers = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_ARRAY_TEXTURE_LAYERS);
173
174 WebGLRenderingContextBase::initializeNewContext();
175
176 // These rely on initialization done in the superclass.
177 ASSERT(m_textureUnits.size() >= 8);
178 m_boundSamplers.clear();
179 m_boundSamplers.resize(m_textureUnits.size());
180
181 // FIXME: this should likely be removed.
182 initializeShaderExtensions();
183}

185void WebGL2RenderingContext::resetUnpackParameters()
186{
187 WebGLRenderingContextBase::resetUnpackParameters();
188
189 if (m_unpackRowLength)
190 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, 0);
191 if (m_unpackImageHeight)
192 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT, 0);
193 if (m_unpackSkipPixels)
194 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS, 0);
195 if (m_unpackSkipRows)
196 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS, 0);
197 if (m_unpackSkipImages)
198 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES, 0);
199}

201void WebGL2RenderingContext::restoreUnpackParameters()
202{
203 WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreUnpackParameters();
204
205 if (m_unpackRowLength)
206 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, m_unpackRowLength);
207 if (m_unpackImageHeight)
208 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT, m_unpackImageHeight);
209 if (m_unpackSkipPixels)
210 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS, m_unpackSkipPixels);
211 if (m_unpackSkipRows)
212 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS, m_unpackSkipRows);
213 if (m_unpackSkipImages)
214 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES, m_unpackSkipImages);
215}

222void WebGL2RenderingContext::initializeVertexArrayObjects()
223{
224 m_defaultVertexArrayObject = WebGLVertexArrayObject::create(*this, WebGLVertexArrayObject::Type::Default);
225 addContextObject(*m_defaultVertexArrayObject);
226#if USE(OPENGL_ES)
227 m_boundVertexArrayObject = m_defaultVertexArrayObject;
228#else
229 bindVertexArray(nullptr); // The default VAO was removed in OpenGL 3.3 but not from WebGL 2; bind the default for WebGL to use.
230#endif
231#if !USE(ANGLE)
232 if (!isGLES2Compliant())
233 initVertexAttrib0();
234#endif
235}

246bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateBufferTarget(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
247{
248 switch (target) {
249 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
250 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_READ_BUFFER:
251 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_WRITE_BUFFER:
252 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
253 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
254 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
255 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
256 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
257 return true;
258 default:
259 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
260 return false;
261 }
262}
263
264bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateBufferTargetCompatibility(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
265{
266 ASSERT(buffer);
267
268 switch (buffer->getTarget()) {
269 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
270 switch (target) {
271 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
272 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
273 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
274 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
275 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
276 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "element array buffers can not be bound to a different target");
277 return false;
278 default:
279 break;
280 }
281 break;
282 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
283 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_READ_BUFFER:
284 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_WRITE_BUFFER:
285 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
286 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
287 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
288 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
289 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER) {
290 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "buffers bound to non ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER targets can not be bound to ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER target");
291 return false;
292 }
293 break;
294 default:
295 break;
296 }
297
298 return true;
299}
300
301WebGLBuffer* WebGL2RenderingContext::validateBufferDataParameters(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLenum usage)
302{
303 WebGLBuffer* buffer = validateBufferDataTarget(functionName, target);
304 if (!buffer)
305 return nullptr;
306 switch (usage) {
307 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_DRAW:
308 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW:
309 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_DRAW:
310 return buffer;
311 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_COPY:
312 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_COPY:
313 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_COPY:
314 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_READ:
315 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_READ:
316 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_READ:
317 return buffer;
318 }
319 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid usage");
320 return nullptr;
321}
322
323WebGLBuffer* WebGL2RenderingContext::validateBufferDataTarget(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
324{
325 WebGLBuffer* buffer = nullptr;
326 switch (target) {
327 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
328 buffer = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer();
329 break;
330 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
331 buffer = m_boundArrayBuffer.get();
332 break;
333 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_READ_BUFFER:
334 buffer = m_boundCopyReadBuffer.get();
335 break;
336 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_WRITE_BUFFER:
337 buffer = m_boundCopyWriteBuffer.get();
338 break;
339 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
340 buffer = m_boundPixelPackBuffer.get();
341 break;
342 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
343 buffer = m_boundPixelUnpackBuffer.get();
344 break;
345 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
346 buffer = m_boundTransformFeedbackBuffer.get();
347 break;
348 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
349 buffer = m_boundUniformBuffer.get();
350 break;
351 default:
352 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
353 return nullptr;
354 }
355 if (!buffer) {
356 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no buffer");
357 return nullptr;
358 }
359 return buffer;
360}

362bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateAndCacheBufferBinding(const AbstractLocker& locker, const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
363{
364 if (!validateBufferTarget(functionName, target))
365 return false;
366
367 if (buffer && !validateBufferTargetCompatibility(functionName, target, buffer))
368 return false;
369
370 switch (target) {
371 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
372 m_boundArrayBuffer = buffer;
373 break;
374 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_READ_BUFFER:
375 m_boundCopyReadBuffer = buffer;
376 break;
377 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_WRITE_BUFFER:
378 m_boundCopyWriteBuffer = buffer;
379 break;
380 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
381 m_boundVertexArrayObject->setElementArrayBuffer(locker, buffer);
382 break;
383 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
384 m_boundPixelPackBuffer = buffer;
385 break;
386 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
387 m_boundPixelUnpackBuffer = buffer;
388 break;
389 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
390 m_boundTransformFeedbackBuffer = buffer;
391 break;
392 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
393 m_boundUniformBuffer = buffer;
394 break;
395 default:
396 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
397 break;
398 }
399
400 if (buffer && !buffer->getTarget())
401 buffer->setTarget(target);
402 return true;
403}

417RefPtr<WebGLTexture> WebGL2RenderingContext::validateTexture3DBinding(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
418{
419 RefPtr<WebGLTexture> texture;
420 switch (target) {
421 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY:
422 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DArrayBinding;
423 break;
424 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D:
425 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture3DBinding;
426 break;
427 default:
428 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture target");
429 return nullptr;
430 }
431 if (!texture)
432 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no texture bound to target");
433 return texture;
434}

436bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateTexFuncLayer(const char* functionName, GCGLenum texTarget, GCGLint layer)
437{
438 if (layer < 0) {
439 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "layer out of range");
440 return false;
441 }
442 switch (texTarget) {
443 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D:
444 if (layer > m_max3DTextureSize - 1) {
445 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "layer out of range");
446 return false;
447 }
448 break;
449 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY:
450 if (layer > m_maxArrayTextureLayers - 1) {
451 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "layer out of range");
452 return false;
453 }
454 break;
455 default:
456 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
457 return false;
458 }
459 return true;
460}

473RefPtr<ArrayBufferView> WebGL2RenderingContext::arrayBufferViewSliceFactory(const char* const functionName, const ArrayBufferView& data, unsigned startByte, unsigned numElements)
474{
475 RefPtr<ArrayBufferView> slice;
476
477 switch (data.getType()) {
478#define FACTORY_CASE(type) \
479 case JSC::Type##type: \
480 slice = JSC::type##Array::tryCreate(data.possiblySharedBuffer(), startByte, numElements); \
481 break;
482
483 FOR_EACH_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE_EXCLUDING_DATA_VIEW(FACTORY_CASE);
484#undef FACTORY_CASE
485 case JSC::TypeDataView:
486 slice = Uint8Array::tryCreate(data.possiblySharedBuffer(), startByte, numElements);
487 break;
488 default:
489 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
490 return nullptr;
491 }
492
493 if (!slice)
494 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::OUT_OF_MEMORY, functionName, "Could not create intermediate ArrayBufferView");
495
496 return slice;
497}
498
499RefPtr<ArrayBufferView> WebGL2RenderingContext::sliceArrayBufferView(const char* const functionName, const ArrayBufferView& data, GCGLuint srcOffset, GCGLuint length)
500{
501 if (data.getType() == JSC::NotTypedArray) {
502 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "Invalid type of Array Buffer View");
503 return nullptr;
504 }
505
506 auto elementSize = JSC::elementSize(data.getType());
507 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedElementSize(elementSize);
508
509 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedSrcOffset(srcOffset);
510 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedByteSrcOffset = checkedSrcOffset * checkedElementSize;
511 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedLength(length);
512 if (!checkedLength) {
513 // Default to the remainder of the buffer.
514 checkedLength = data.byteLength();
515 checkedLength /= elementSize;
516 checkedLength -= srcOffset;
517 }
518 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedByteLength = checkedLength * checkedElementSize;
519
520 if (checkedLength.hasOverflowed() || checkedByteSrcOffset.hasOverflowed()
521 || checkedByteLength.hasOverflowed()
522 || checkedByteSrcOffset > data.byteLength()
523 || checkedByteLength > data.byteLength() - checkedByteSrcOffset.value()) {
524 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "srcOffset or length is out of bounds");
525 return nullptr;
526 }
527
528 return arrayBufferViewSliceFactory(functionName, data, data.byteOffset() + checkedByteSrcOffset.value(), checkedLength);
529}

531void WebGL2RenderingContext::pixelStorei(GCGLenum pname, GCGLint param)
532{
533 if (isContextLostOrPending())
534 return;
535 if (param < 0) {
536 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "pixelStorei", "negative value");
537 return;
538 }
539 switch (pname) {
540 case GraphicsContextGL::PACK_ROW_LENGTH:
541 m_packRowLength = param;
542 break;
543 case GraphicsContextGL::PACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
544 m_packSkipPixels = param;
545 break;
546 case GraphicsContextGL::PACK_SKIP_ROWS:
547 m_packSkipRows = param;
548 break;
549 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH:
550 m_unpackRowLength = param;
551 break;
552 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT:
553 m_unpackImageHeight = param;
554 break;
555 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS:
556 m_unpackSkipPixels = param;
557 break;
558 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS:
559 m_unpackSkipRows = param;
560 break;
561 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES:
562 m_unpackSkipImages = param;
563 break;
564 default:
565 WebGLRenderingContextBase::pixelStorei(pname, param);
566 return;
567 }
568 m_context->pixelStorei(pname, param);
569}

583void WebGL2RenderingContext::copyBufferSubData(GCGLenum readTarget, GCGLenum writeTarget, GCGLint64 readOffset, GCGLint64 writeOffset, GCGLint64 size)
584{
585 if (isContextLostOrPending())
586 return;
587
588 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> readBuffer = validateBufferDataParameters("copyBufferSubData", readTarget, GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW);
589 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> writeBuffer = validateBufferDataParameters("copyBufferSubData", writeTarget, GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW);
590 if (!readBuffer || !writeBuffer) {
591 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "copyBufferSubData", "Invalid readTarget or writeTarget");
592 return;
593 }
594
595 if (readOffset < 0 || writeOffset < 0 || size < 0) {
596 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyBufferSubData", "offset < 0");
597 return;
598 }
599
600 if ((readBuffer->getTarget() == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER && writeBuffer->getTarget() != GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER)
601 || (writeBuffer->getTarget() == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER && readBuffer->getTarget() != GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER)) {
602 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "copyBufferSubData", "Cannot copy into an element buffer destination from a non-element buffer source");
603 return;
604 }
605
606 Checked<GCGLintptr, RecordOverflow> checkedReadOffset(readOffset);
607 Checked<GCGLintptr, RecordOverflow> checkedWriteOffset(writeOffset);
608 Checked<GCGLsizeiptr, RecordOverflow> checkedSize(size);
609 if (checkedReadOffset.hasOverflowed() || checkedWriteOffset.hasOverflowed() || checkedSize.hasOverflowed()) {
610 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyBufferSubData", "Offset or size is too big");
611 return;
612 }
613
614 if (!writeBuffer->associateCopyBufferSubData(*readBuffer, checkedReadOffset, checkedWriteOffset, checkedSize)) {
615 this->synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyBufferSubData", "offset out of range");
616 return;
617 }
618
619 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
620#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
621 m_context->copyBufferSubData(readTarget, writeTarget, checkedReadOffset, checkedWriteOffset, checkedSize);
622#endif
623 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
624 // The bufferSubData function failed. Tell the buffer it doesn't have the data it thinks it does.
625 writeBuffer->disassociateBufferData();
626 }
627}
628
629void WebGL2RenderingContext::getBufferSubData(GCGLenum target, long long srcByteOffset, RefPtr<ArrayBufferView>&& dstData, GCGLuint dstOffset, GCGLuint length)
630{
631 if (isContextLostOrPending())
632 return;
633 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> buffer = validateBufferDataParameters("getBufferSubData", target, GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW);
634 if (!buffer) {
635 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getBufferSubData", "No WebGLBuffer is bound to target");
636 return;
637 }
638
639 // FIXME: Implement "If target is TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER, and any transform feedback object is currently active, an INVALID_OPERATION error is generated."
640
641 if (!dstData) {
642 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getBufferSubData", "Null dstData");
643 return;
644 }
645
646 if (dstData->getType() == JSC::NotTypedArray) {
647 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getBufferSubData", "Invalid type of Array Buffer View");
648 return;
649 }
650
651 auto elementSize = JSC::elementSize(dstData->getType());
652 auto dstDataLength = dstData->byteLength() / elementSize;
653
654 if (dstOffset > dstDataLength) {
655 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getBufferSubData", "dstOffset is larger than the length of the destination buffer.");
656 return;
657 }
658
659 GCGLuint copyLength = length ? length : dstDataLength - dstOffset;
660
661 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedDstOffset(dstOffset);
662 Checked<GCGLuint, RecordOverflow> checkedCopyLength(copyLength);
663 auto checkedDestinationEnd = checkedDstOffset + checkedCopyLength;
664 if (checkedDestinationEnd.hasOverflowed()) {
665 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getBufferSubData", "dstOffset + copyLength is too high");
666 return;
667 }
668
669 if (checkedDestinationEnd > dstDataLength) {
670 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getBufferSubData", "end of written destination is past the end of the buffer");
671 return;
672 }
673
674 if (srcByteOffset < 0) {
675 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getBufferSubData", "srcByteOffset is less than 0");
676 return;
677 }
678
679 Checked<GCGLintptr, RecordOverflow> checkedSrcByteOffset(srcByteOffset);
680 Checked<GCGLintptr, RecordOverflow> checkedCopyLengthPtr(copyLength);
681 Checked<GCGLintptr, RecordOverflow> checkedElementSize(elementSize);
682 auto checkedSourceEnd = checkedSrcByteOffset + checkedCopyLengthPtr * checkedElementSize;
683 if (checkedSourceEnd.hasOverflowed() || checkedSourceEnd > buffer->byteLength()) {
684 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getBufferSubData", "Parameters would read outside the bounds of the source buffer");
685 return;
686 }
687
688 if (!copyLength)
689 return;
690
691 // FIXME: Coalesce multiple getBufferSubData() calls to use a single map() call
692 m_context->getBufferSubData(target, srcByteOffset, makeGCGLSpan(static_cast<char*>(dstData->baseAddress()) + dstData->byteOffset() + dstOffset * elementSize, copyLength * elementSize));
693}

695void WebGL2RenderingContext::bindFramebuffer(GCGLenum target, WebGLFramebuffer* buffer)
696{
697 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
698
699 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindFramebuffer", buffer))
700 return;
701
702 switch (target) {
703 case GraphicsContextGL::DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER:
704 break;
705 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER:
706 case GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER:
707 m_readFramebufferBinding = buffer;
708 break;
709 default:
710 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "bindFramebuffer", "invalid target");
711 return;
712 }
713
714 setFramebuffer(locker, target, buffer);
715}

725void WebGL2RenderingContext::deleteFramebuffer(WebGLFramebuffer* framebuffer)
726{
727 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
728
729 if (!deleteObject(locker, framebuffer))
730 return;
731
732 GCGLenum target = 0;
733 if (framebuffer == m_framebufferBinding) {
734 if (framebuffer == m_readFramebufferBinding) {
735 target = GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER;
736 m_framebufferBinding = nullptr;
737 m_readFramebufferBinding = nullptr;
738 } else {
739 target = GraphicsContextGL::DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER;
740 m_framebufferBinding = nullptr;
741 }
742 m_context->bindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER, 0);
743 } else if (framebuffer == m_readFramebufferBinding) {
744 target = GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER;
745 m_readFramebufferBinding = nullptr;
746 }
747 if (target)
748 m_context->bindFramebuffer(target, 0);
749}

751void WebGL2RenderingContext::framebufferTextureLayer(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum attachment, WebGLTexture* texture, GCGLint level, GCGLint layer)
752{
753 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateFramebufferFuncParameters("framebufferTextureLayer", target, attachment))
754 return;
755
756 if (texture && !validateWebGLObject("framebufferTextureLayer", texture))
757 return;
758
759 GCGLenum texTarget = texture ? texture->getTarget() : 0;
760 if (texture) {
761 if (texTarget != GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D && texTarget != GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY) {
762 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferTextureLayer", "invalid texture type");
763 return;
764 }
765 if (!validateTexFuncLayer("framebufferTextureLayer", texTarget, layer))
766 return;
767 if (!validateTexFuncLevel("framebufferTextureLayer", texTarget, level))
768 return;
769 }
770 WebGLFramebuffer* framebufferBinding = getFramebufferBinding(target);
771 if (!framebufferBinding || !framebufferBinding->object()) {
772 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferTextureLayer", "no framebuffer bound");
773 return;
774 }
775 framebufferBinding->setAttachmentForBoundFramebuffer(target, attachment, texTarget, texture, level, layer);
776 applyStencilTest();
777}

783 switch (internalformat) {

799 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8:

801 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB5_A1:

807 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16UI:
808 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16I:

822
823WebGLAny WebGL2RenderingContext::getInternalformatParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLenum pname)
824{
825 if (isContextLostOrPending())
826 return nullptr;
827
828 if (pname != GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLES) {
829 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getInternalformatParameter", "invalid parameter name");
830 return nullptr;
831 }
832
833#if USE(OPENGL_ES) || USE(ANGLE)
834 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
835 GCGLint numValues = m_context->getInternalformati(target, internalformat, GraphicsContextGL::NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS);
836 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList() || numValues < 0)
837 return nullptr;
838
839 // Integer formats do not support multisampling, so numValues == 0 may occur.
840
841 Vector<GCGLint> params(numValues);
842 if (numValues > 0) {
843 m_context->getInternalformativ(target, internalformat, pname, params);
844 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList())
845 return nullptr;
846 }
847#else
848 // On desktop OpenGL 4.1 or below we must emulate glGetInternalformativ.
849
850 // GL_INVALID_ENUM is generated if target is not GL_RENDERBUFFER.
851 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER) {
852 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getInternalformatParameter", "invalid target");
853 return nullptr;
854 }
855
856 // GL_INVALID_ENUM is generated if internalformat is not color-, depth-, or stencil-renderable.
857 if (!isRenderableInternalformat(internalformat)) {
858 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getInternalformatParameter", "invalid internal format");
859 return nullptr;
860 }
861
862 Vector<GCGLint> samples;
863 // The way I understand this is that this will return a MINIMUM numSamples for all accepeted internalformats.
864 // However, the true value of this on supported GL versions is gleaned via a getInternalformativ call that depends on internalformat.
865 int numSamplesMask = getIntParameter(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_SAMPLES);
866
867 while (numSamplesMask > 0) {
868 samples.append(numSamplesMask);
869 numSamplesMask = numSamplesMask >> 1;
870 }
871
872 // Since multisampling is not supported for signed and unsigned integer internal formats,
873 // the value of GL_NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS will be zero for such formats.
874 GCGLint numValues = isIntegerFormat(internalformat) ? 0 : samples.size();
875 Vector<GCGLint> params(numValues);
876 for (size_t i = 0; i < static_cast<size_t>(numValues); ++i)
877 params[i] = samples[i];
878#endif
879
880 return Int32Array::tryCreate(params.data(), params.size());
881}

905void WebGL2RenderingContext::readBuffer(GCGLenum src)
906{
907 if (src == GraphicsContextGL::BACK) {
908 // Because the backbuffer is simulated on all current WebKit ports, we need to change BACK to COLOR_ATTACHMENT0.
909 if (m_readFramebufferBinding) {
910 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "readBuffer", "BACK is valid for default framebuffer only");
911 return;
912 }
913 src = GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0;
914 } else if (!m_readFramebufferBinding && src != GraphicsContextGL::NONE) {
915 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "readBuffer", "default framebuffer only supports NONE or BACK");
916 return;
917 }
918
919 m_context->readBuffer(src);
920}

1034WebGLAny WebGL2RenderingContext::getTexParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname)
1035{
1036 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateTextureBinding("getTexParameter", target))
1037 return nullptr;

1040 FALLTHROUGH;

1042 FALLTHROUGH;

1054 FALLTHROUGH;
1055 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:

1641 if (index < m_maxVertexAttribs) {
1642 m_vertexAttribValue[index].type = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
1643 m_vertexAttribValue[index].iValue[0] = x;

1650void WebGL2RenderingContext::vertexAttribI4iv(GCGLuint index, Int32List&& list)
1651{
1652 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1653 return;
1654 auto data = list.data();
1655 if (!data) {
1656 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribI4iv", "no array");
1657 return;
1658 }
1659
1660 int size = list.length();
1661 if (size < 4) {
1662 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribI4iv", "array too small");
1663 return;
1664 }
1665 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
1666 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribI4iv", "index out of range");
1667 return;
1668 }
1669 m_context->vertexAttribI4iv(index, makeGCGLSpan<4>(data));
1670 m_vertexAttribValue[index].type = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
1671 memcpy(m_vertexAttribValue[index].iValue, data, sizeof(m_vertexAttribValue[index].iValue));
1672}

1698 int size = list.length();
1699 if (size < 4) {
1700 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribI4uiv", "array too small");
1701 return;
1702 }
1703 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
1704 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribI4uiv", "index out of range");
1705 return;
1706 }
1707 m_context->vertexAttribI4uiv(index, makeGCGLSpan<4>(data));
1708 m_vertexAttribValue[index].type = GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT;
1709 memcpy(m_vertexAttribValue[index].uiValue, data, sizeof(m_vertexAttribValue[index].uiValue));
1710}
1711
1712void WebGL2RenderingContext::vertexAttribIPointer(GCGLuint index, GCGLint size, GCGLenum type, GCGLsizei stride, GCGLint64 offset)
1713{
1714 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1715
1716 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1717 return;
1718
1719 switch (type) {
1720 case GraphicsContextGL::BYTE:
1721 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1722 case GraphicsContextGL::SHORT:
1723 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1724 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
1725 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
1726 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
1727 break;
1728 default:
1729 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "vertexAttribIPointer", "invalid type");
1730 return;
1731 }
1732 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
1733 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribIPointer", "index out of range");
1734 return;
1735 }
1736 if (size < 1 || size > 4) {
1737 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribIPointer", "bad size");
1738 return;
1739 }
1740 if (stride < 0 || stride > 255) {
1741 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribIPointer", "bad stride");
1742 return;
1743 }
1744 if (offset < 0 || offset > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()) {
1745 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribIPointer", "bad offset");
1746 return;
1747 }
1748 if (!m_boundArrayBuffer && offset) {
1749 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "vertexAttribIPointer", "no bound ARRAY_BUFFER");
1750 return;
1751 }
1752 // Determine the number of elements the bound buffer can hold, given the offset, size, type and stride.
1753 auto typeSize = sizeInBytes(type);
1754 if (!typeSize) {
1755 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "vertexAttribIPointer", "invalid type");
1756 return;
1757 }
1758 if ((stride % typeSize) || (static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset) % typeSize)) {
1759 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "vertexAttribIPointer", "stride or offset not valid for type");
1760 return;
1761 }
1762 GCGLsizei bytesPerElement = size * typeSize;
1763
1764 m_boundVertexArrayObject->setVertexAttribState(locker, index, bytesPerElement, size, type, false, stride, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), true, m_boundArrayBuffer.get());
1765 m_context->vertexAttribIPointer(index, size, type, stride, offset);
1766}

1800void WebGL2RenderingContext::drawBuffers(const Vector<GCGLenum>& buffers)
1801{
1802 if (isContextLost())
1803 return;
1804 GCGLsizei n = buffers.size();
1805 const GCGLenum* bufs = buffers.data();
1806 for (GCGLsizei i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1807 switch (bufs[i]) {
1808 case GraphicsContextGL::NONE:
1809 case GraphicsContextGL::BACK:
1810 case GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0:
1811 continue;
1812 default:
1813 if (bufs[i] > GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0
1814 && bufs[i] < GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + getMaxColorAttachments()) {
1815 continue;
1816 }
1817 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "drawBuffers", "invalid buffer");
1818 return;
1819 }
1820 }
1821 if (!m_framebufferBinding) {
1822 if (n != 1) {
1823 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawBuffers", "more than one buffer");
1824 return;
1825 }
1826 if (bufs[0] != GraphicsContextGL::BACK && bufs[0] != GraphicsContextGL::NONE) {
1827 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawBuffers", "BACK or NONE");
1828 return;
1829 }
1830 // Because the backbuffer is simulated on all current WebKit ports, we need to change BACK to COLOR_ATTACHMENT0.
1831 GCGLenum value[1] { (bufs[0] == GraphicsContextGL::BACK) ? GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 : GraphicsContextGL::NONE };
1832 m_context->drawBuffers(value);
1833 setBackDrawBuffer(bufs[0]);
1834 } else {
1835 if (n > getMaxDrawBuffers()) {
1836 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "drawBuffers", "more than max draw buffers");
1837 return;
1838 }
1839 for (GCGLsizei i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1840 if (bufs[i] != GraphicsContextGL::NONE && bufs[i] != static_cast<GCGLenum>(GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + i)) {
1841 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawBuffers", "COLOR_ATTACHMENTi or NONE");
1842 return;
1843 }
1844 }
1845 m_framebufferBinding->drawBuffers(buffers);
1846 }
1847}

1935bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateQueryTarget(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLenum* targetKey)
1936{
1937 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED && target != GraphicsContextGL::ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_CONSERVATIVE && target != GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_PRIMITIVES_WRITTEN) {
1938 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
1939 return false;
1940 }
1941 if (targetKey)
1942 *targetKey = (target == GraphicsContextGL::ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED_CONSERVATIVE) ? GraphicsContextGL::ANY_SAMPLES_PASSED : target;
1943 return true;
1944}
1945
1946void WebGL2RenderingContext::beginQuery(GCGLenum target, WebGLQuery& query)
1947{
1948 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1949
1950 GCGLenum targetKey;
1951 if (!validateWebGLObject("beginQuery", &query) || !validateQueryTarget("beginQuery", target, &targetKey))
1952 return;
1953
1954 if (query.target() && query.target() != target) {
1955 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginQuery", "query type does not match target");
1956 return;
1957 }
1958
1959 auto addResult = m_activeQueries.add(targetKey, makeRefPtr(&query));
1960
1961 // Only one query object can be active per target.
1962 if (!addResult.isNewEntry) {
1963 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginQuery", "Query object of target is already active");
1964 return;
1965 }
1966
1967 m_context->beginQuery(target, query.object());
1968 query.setTarget(target);
1969}
1970
1971void WebGL2RenderingContext::endQuery(GCGLenum target)
1972{
1973 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1974
1975 GCGLenum targetKey;
1976 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !scriptExecutionContext() || !validateQueryTarget("beginQuery", target, &targetKey))
1977 return;
1978
1979 auto query = m_activeQueries.take(targetKey);
1980 if (!query) {
1981 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "endQuery", "Query object of target is not active");
1982 return;
1983 }
1984
1985 m_context->endQuery(target);
1986
1987 // A query's result must not be made available until control has returned to the user agent's main loop.
1988 scriptExecutionContext()->eventLoop().queueMicrotask([query] {
1989 query->makeResultAvailable();
1990 });
1991}
1992
1993RefPtr<WebGLQuery> WebGL2RenderingContext::getQuery(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname)
1994{
1995 GCGLenum targetKey;
1996 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !scriptExecutionContext() || !validateQueryTarget("beginQuery", target, &targetKey))
1997 return nullptr;
1998
1999 if (pname != GraphicsContextGL::CURRENT_QUERY) {
2000 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getQuery", "invalid parameter name");
2001 return nullptr;
2002 }
2003
2004 auto query = m_activeQueries.get(targetKey);
2005 if (!query || query->target() != target)
2006 return nullptr;
2007 return query;
2008}

2010WebGLAny WebGL2RenderingContext::getQueryParameter(WebGLQuery& query, GCGLenum pname)
2011{

2013 return nullptr;
2014

2016 case GraphicsContextGL::QUERY_RESULT:
2017 if (!query.isResultAvailable())
2018 return false;
2019 break;
2020 case GraphicsContextGL::QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE:

2022 return false;
2023 break;
2024 default:
2025 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getQueryParameter", "Invalid pname");
2026 return nullptr;
2027 }
2028
2029 return static_cast<unsigned>(m_context->getQueryObjectui(query.object(), pname));
2030}

2302void WebGL2RenderingContext::beginTransformFeedback(GCGLenum primitiveMode)
2303{
2304 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2305 return;
2306
2307 if (!ValidateTransformFeedbackPrimitiveMode(primitiveMode)) {
2308 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "beginTransformFeedback", "invalid transform feedback primitive mode");
2309 return;
2310 }
2311 if (!m_currentProgram) {
2312 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginTransformFeedback", "no program is active");
2313 return;
2314 }
2315 if (m_boundTransformFeedback->isActive()) {
2316 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginTransformFeedback", "transform feedback is already active");
2317 return;
2318 }
2319 int requiredBufferCount = m_currentProgram->requiredTransformFeedbackBufferCount();
2320 if (!requiredBufferCount) {
2321 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginTransformFeedback", "current active program does not specify any transform feedback varyings to record");
2322 return;
2323 }
2324 if (!m_boundTransformFeedback->hasEnoughBuffers(requiredBufferCount)) {
2325 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "beginTransformFeedback", "not enough transform feedback buffers bound");
2326 return;
2327 }
2328
2329 m_context->beginTransformFeedback(primitiveMode);
2330
2331 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2332 m_boundTransformFeedback->setProgram(locker, *m_currentProgram);
2333 m_boundTransformFeedback->setActive(true);
2334 m_boundTransformFeedback->setPaused(false);
2335}

2347 m_context->endTransformFeedback();
2348
2349 m_boundTransformFeedback->setPaused(false);
2350 m_boundTransformFeedback->setActive(false);
2351}
2352
2353void WebGL2RenderingContext::transformFeedbackVaryings(WebGLProgram& program, const Vector<String>& varyings, GCGLenum bufferMode)
2354{
2355 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("transformFeedbackVaryings", &program))
2356 return;
2357
2358 switch (bufferMode) {
2359 case GraphicsContextGL::SEPARATE_ATTRIBS:
2360 if (varyings.size() > m_maxTransformFeedbackSeparateAttribs) {
2361 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "transformFeedbackVaryings", "too many varyings");
2362 return;
2363 }
2364 break;
2365 case GraphicsContextGL::INTERLEAVED_ATTRIBS:
2366 break;
2367 default:
2368 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "transformFeedbackVaryings", "invalid buffer mode");
2369 return;
2370 }
2371 program.setRequiredTransformFeedbackBufferCount(bufferMode == GraphicsContextGL::INTERLEAVED_ATTRIBS ? 1 : varyings.size());
2372
2373 m_context->transformFeedbackVaryings(program.object(), varyings, bufferMode);
2374}

2376RefPtr<WebGLActiveInfo> WebGL2RenderingContext::getTransformFeedbackVarying(WebGLProgram& program, GCGLuint index)
2377{
2378 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getTransformFeedbackVarying", &program))
2379 return nullptr;
2380
2381 GraphicsContextGL::ActiveInfo info;
2382 m_context->getTransformFeedbackVarying(program.object(), index, info);
2383
2384 if (!info.name || !info.type || !info.size)
2385 return nullptr;
2386
2387 return WebGLActiveInfo::create(info.name, info.type, info.size);
2388}

2390void WebGL2RenderingContext::pauseTransformFeedback()
2391{
2392 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2393 return;
2394
2395 if (!m_boundTransformFeedback->isActive()) {
2396 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "pauseTransformFeedback", "transform feedback is not active");
2397 return;
2398 }
2399
2400 if (m_boundTransformFeedback->isPaused()) {
2401 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "pauseTransformFeedback", "transform feedback is already paused");
2402 return;
2403 }
2404
2405 m_boundTransformFeedback->setPaused(true);
2406 m_context->pauseTransformFeedback();
2407}
2408
2409void WebGL2RenderingContext::resumeTransformFeedback()
2410{
2411 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2412 return;
2413
2414 if (!m_boundTransformFeedback->validateProgramForResume(m_currentProgram.get())) {
2415 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "resumeTransformFeedback", "the current program is not the same as when beginTransformFeedback was called");
2416 return;
2417 }
2418 if (!m_boundTransformFeedback->isActive() || !m_boundTransformFeedback->isPaused()) {
2419 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "resumeTransformFeedback", "transform feedback is not active or not paused");
2420 return;
2421 }
2422
2423 m_boundTransformFeedback->setPaused(false);
2424 m_context->resumeTransformFeedback();
2425}

2427bool WebGL2RenderingContext::setIndexedBufferBinding(const char *functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLuint index, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
2428{
2429 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2430
2431 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject(functionName, buffer))
2432 return false;
2433
2434 switch (target) {
2435 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
2436 if (index >= m_maxTransformFeedbackSeparateAttribs) {
2437 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "index out of range");
2438 return false;
2439 }
2440 break;
2441 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
2442 if (index >= m_boundIndexedUniformBuffers.size()) {
2443 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "index out of range");
2444 return false;
2445 }
2446 break;
2447 default:
2448 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
2449 return false;
2450 }
2451
2452 if (!validateAndCacheBufferBinding(locker, functionName, target, buffer))
2453 return false;
2454
2455 switch (target) {
2456 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
2457 m_boundTransformFeedback->setBoundIndexedTransformFeedbackBuffer(locker, index, buffer);
2458 break;
2459 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
2460 m_boundIndexedUniformBuffers[index] = buffer;
2461 break;
2462 default:
2463 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
2464 return false;
2465 }
2466 return true;
2467}
2468
2469void WebGL2RenderingContext::bindBufferBase(GCGLenum target, GCGLuint index, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
2470{
2471 if (setIndexedBufferBinding("bindBufferBase", target, index, buffer))
2472 m_context->bindBufferBase(target, index, objectOrZero(buffer));
2473}
2474
2475void WebGL2RenderingContext::bindBufferRange(GCGLenum target, GCGLuint index, WebGLBuffer* buffer, GCGLint64 offset, GCGLint64 size)
2476{
2477 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER && (offset % 4 || size % 4)) {
2478 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bindBufferRange", "invalid offset or size");
2479 return;
2480 }
2481 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER && (offset % m_uniformBufferOffsetAlignment)) {
2482 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bindBufferRange", "invalid offset");
2483 return;
2484 }
2485 if (setIndexedBufferBinding("bindBufferRange", target, index, buffer))
2486 m_context->bindBufferRange(target, index, objectOrZero(buffer), offset, size);
2487}

2619void WebGL2RenderingContext::deleteVertexArray(WebGLVertexArrayObject* arrayObject)
2620{
2621 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2622
2623 // validateWebGLObject generates an error if the object has already been
2624 // deleted, so we must replicate most of its checks here.
2625 if (!arrayObject || isContextLost())
2626 return;
2627
2628 if (!arrayObject->validate(contextGroup(), *this)) {
2629 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "deleteVertexArray", "object does not belong to this context");
2630 return;
2631 }
2632
2633 if (arrayObject->isDeleted())
2634 return;
2635
2636 if (!arrayObject->isDefaultObject() && arrayObject == m_boundVertexArrayObject) {
2637 // bindVertexArray grabs the lock internally.
2638 DropLockForScope noLockScope(locker);
2639 bindVertexArray(nullptr); // The default VAO was removed in OpenGL 3.3 but not from WebGL 2; bind the default for WebGL to use.
2640 }
2641
2642 arrayObject->deleteObject(locker, graphicsContextGL());
2643}

2645GCGLboolean WebGL2RenderingContext::isVertexArray(WebGLVertexArrayObject* arrayObject)
2646{
2647 if (!arrayObject || isContextLost() || !arrayObject->validate(0, *this))
2648 return false;
2649
2650 if (!arrayObject->hasEverBeenBound())
2651 return false;
2652 if (arrayObject->isDeleted())
2653 return false;
2654
2655 return m_context->isVertexArray(arrayObject->object());
2656}

2658void WebGL2RenderingContext::bindVertexArray(WebGLVertexArrayObject* arrayObject)
2659{
2660 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2661
2662 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindVertexArray", arrayObject))
2663 return;
2664
2665 if (arrayObject && !arrayObject->isDefaultObject() && arrayObject->object()) {
2666 m_context->bindVertexArray(arrayObject->object());
2667
2668 arrayObject->setHasEverBeenBound();
2669 setBoundVertexArrayObject(locker, arrayObject);
2670 } else {
2671 m_context->bindVertexArray(m_defaultVertexArrayObject->object());
2672 setBoundVertexArrayObject(locker, m_defaultVertexArrayObject.get());
2673 }

2739 result.append("WEBKIT_WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc"_s);
2740 result.append("WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc"_s);

2763
2764static bool validateDefaultFramebufferAttachment(GCGLenum& attachment)
2765{
2766 switch (attachment) {
2767 case GraphicsContextGL::BACK:
2768 // Because the backbuffer is simulated on all current WebKit ports, we need to change BACK to COLOR_ATTACHMENT0.
2769 attachment = GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0;
2770 return true;
2771 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH:
2772 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL:
2773 return true;
2774 }
2775
2776 return false;
2777}
2778
2779WebGLAny WebGL2RenderingContext::getFramebufferAttachmentParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum attachment, GCGLenum pname)
2780{
2781 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2782 return nullptr;
2783
2784 const char* functionName = "getFramebufferAttachmentParameter";
2785 if (!validateFramebufferTarget(target)) {
2786 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
2787 return nullptr;
2788 }
2789 auto targetFramebuffer = (target == GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER) ? m_readFramebufferBinding : m_framebufferBinding;
2790
2791 if (!targetFramebuffer) {
2792 if (!validateDefaultFramebufferAttachment(attachment)) {
2793 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid attachment");
2794 return nullptr;
2795 }
2796
2797 // We can look directly at m_attributes because in WebGL 2,
2798 // they are required to be honored.
2799 bool hasDepth = m_attributes.depth;
2800 bool hasStencil = m_attributes.stencil;
2801 bool missingImage = (attachment == GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH && !hasDepth) || (attachment == GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL && !hasStencil);
2802 if (missingImage) {
2803 switch (pname) {
2804 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
2805 return static_cast<unsigned>(GraphicsContextGL::NONE);
2806 default:
2807 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid parameter name");
2808 return nullptr;
2809 }
2810 }
2811
2812 switch (pname) {
2813 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
2814 return GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_DEFAULT;
2815 default:
2816 return m_context->getFramebufferAttachmentParameteri(target, attachment, pname);
2817 }
2818 }
2819
2820#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
2821 if (targetFramebuffer->isOpaque()) {
2822 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getFramebufferAttachmentParameter", "An opaque framebuffer's attachments cannot be inspected or changed");
2823 return nullptr;
2824 }
2825#endif
2826
2827 if (!validateNonDefaultFramebufferAttachment(functionName, attachment))
2828 return nullptr;
2829
2830 RefPtr<WebGLSharedObject> attachmentObject;
2831 if (attachment == GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT) {
2832 attachmentObject = makeRefPtr(targetFramebuffer->getAttachmentObject(GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_ATTACHMENT));
2833 auto stencilAttachment = makeRefPtr(targetFramebuffer->getAttachmentObject(GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_ATTACHMENT));
2834 if (attachmentObject != stencilAttachment) {
2835 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "different objects bound to DEPTH_ATTACHMENT and STENCIL_ATTACHMENT");
2836 return nullptr;
2837 }
2838 } else
2839 attachmentObject = makeRefPtr(targetFramebuffer->getAttachmentObject(attachment));
2840
2841 if (!attachmentObject) {
2842 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE)
2843 return static_cast<unsigned>(GraphicsContextGL::NONE);
2844 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME)
2845 return nullptr;
2846 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid parameter name");
2847 return nullptr;
2848 }
2849
2850 switch (pname) {
2851 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
2852 if (attachmentObject->isTexture())
2853 return static_cast<unsigned>(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE);
2854 return static_cast<unsigned>(GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER);
2855 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
2856 if (attachmentObject->isTexture())
2857 return makeRefPtr(reinterpret_cast<WebGLTexture&>(*attachmentObject));
2858 return makeRefPtr(reinterpret_cast<WebGLRenderbuffer&>(*attachmentObject));
2859 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_FACE:
2860 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LAYER:
2861 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LEVEL:
2862 if (!attachmentObject->isTexture())
2863 break;
2864 FALLTHROUGH;
2865 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_RED_SIZE:
2866 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_GREEN_SIZE:
2867 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_BLUE_SIZE:
2868 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_ALPHA_SIZE:
2869 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_DEPTH_SIZE:
2870 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_STENCIL_SIZE:
2871 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING:
2872 return m_context->getFramebufferAttachmentParameteri(target, attachment, pname);
2873 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COMPONENT_TYPE:
2874 if (attachment == GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT) {
2875 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "COMPONENT_TYPE can't be queried for DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT");

2877 }
2878 return m_context->getFramebufferAttachmentParameteri(target, attachment, pname);
2879 }

2881 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid parameter name for attachment");
2882 return nullptr;
2883}

2949void WebGL2RenderingContext::renderbufferStorageImpl(GCGLenum target, GCGLsizei samples, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, const char* functionName)
2950{
2951 switch (internalformat) {
2952 case GraphicsContextGL::R8UI:
2953 case GraphicsContextGL::R8I:
2954 case GraphicsContextGL::R16UI:
2955 case GraphicsContextGL::R16I:
2956 case GraphicsContextGL::R32UI:
2957 case GraphicsContextGL::R32I:
2958 case GraphicsContextGL::RG8UI:
2959 case GraphicsContextGL::RG8I:
2960 case GraphicsContextGL::RG16UI:
2961 case GraphicsContextGL::RG16I:
2962 case GraphicsContextGL::RG32UI:
2963 case GraphicsContextGL::RG32I:
2964 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8UI:
2965 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8I:
2966 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB10_A2UI:
2967 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16UI:
2968 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16I:
2969 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA32UI:
2970 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA32I:
2971 if (samples > 0) {
2972 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "for integer formats, samples > 0 is not allowed");
2973 return;
2974 }
2975 FALLTHROUGH;
2976 case GraphicsContextGL::R8:
2977 case GraphicsContextGL::RG8:
2978 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB8:
2979 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB565:
2980 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8:
2981 case GraphicsContextGL::SRGB8_ALPHA8:
2982 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB5_A1:
2983 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA4:
2984 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB10_A2:
2985 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT16:
2986 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT24:
2987 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT32F:
2988 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH24_STENCIL8:
2989 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH32F_STENCIL8:
2990 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_INDEX8:
2991 renderbufferStorageHelper(target, samples, internalformat, width, height);
2992 break;
2993 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL:
2994 // To be WebGL 1 backward compatible.
2995 if (samples) {
2996 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
2997 return;
2998 }
2999 renderbufferStorageHelper(target, 0, GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH24_STENCIL8, width, height);
3000 break;
3001 case GraphicsContextGL::R16F:
3002 case GraphicsContextGL::RG16F:
3003 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16F:
3004 if (!extensionIsEnabled("EXT_color_buffer_float"_s) && !extensionIsEnabled("EXT_color_buffer_half_float"_s)) {
3005 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "EXT_color_buffer_float or EXT_color_buffer_half_float not enabled");
3006 return;
3007 }
3008 renderbufferStorageHelper(target, samples, internalformat, width, height);
3009 break;
3010 case GraphicsContextGL::R32F:
3011 case GraphicsContextGL::RG32F:
3012 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA32F:
3013 case GraphicsContextGL::R11F_G11F_B10F:
3014 if (!extensionIsEnabled("EXT_color_buffer_float"_s)) {
3015 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "EXT_color_buffer_float not enabled");
3016 return;
3017 }
3018 renderbufferStorageHelper(target, samples, internalformat, width, height);
3019 break;
3020 default:
3021 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
3022 return;
3023 }
3024 m_renderbufferBinding->setInternalFormat(internalformat);
3025 m_renderbufferBinding->setSize(width, height);
3026 m_renderbufferBinding->setIsValid(true);

3066bool WebGL2RenderingContext::checkAndTranslateAttachments(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, Vector<GCGLenum>& attachments)
3067{
3068 if (!validateFramebufferTarget(target)) {
3069 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
3070 return false;
3071 }
3072
3073 if (!getFramebufferBinding(target)) {
3074 // For the default framebuffer, translate GL_COLOR/GL_DEPTH/GL_STENCIL.
3075 // The default framebuffer of WebGL is not fb 0, it is an internal fbo.
3076 for (size_t i = 0; i < attachments.size(); ++i) {
3077 switch (attachments[i]) {
3078 case GraphicsContextGL::COLOR:
3079 attachments[i] = GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0;
3080 break;
3081 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH:
3082 attachments[i] = GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_ATTACHMENT;
3083 break;
3084 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL:
3085 attachments[i] = GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_ATTACHMENT;
3086 break;
3087 default:
3088 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid attachment");
3089 return false;
3090 }
3091 }
3092 }
3093 return true;
3094}

3359
3360bool WebGL2RenderingContext::validateIndexArrayConservative(GCGLenum type, unsigned& numElementsRequired)
3361{
3362 // Performs conservative validation by caching a maximum index of
3363 // the given type per element array buffer. If all of the bound
3364 // array buffers have enough elements to satisfy that maximum
3365 // index, skips the expensive per-draw-call iteration in
3366 // validateIndexArrayPrecise.
3367
3368 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> elementArrayBuffer = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer();
3369
3370 if (!elementArrayBuffer)
3371 return false;
3372
3373 GCGLsizeiptr numElements = elementArrayBuffer->byteLength();
3374 // The case count==0 is already dealt with in drawElements before validateIndexArrayConservative.
3375 if (!numElements)
3376 return false;
3377 auto buffer = elementArrayBuffer->elementArrayBuffer();
3378 ASSERT(buffer);
3379
3380 std::optional<unsigned> maxIndex = elementArrayBuffer->getCachedMaxIndex(type);
3381 if (!maxIndex) {
3382 // Compute the maximum index in the entire buffer for the given type of index.
3383 switch (type) {
3384 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
3385 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLubyte>(buffer, 0, numElements);
3386 break;
3387 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
3388 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLushort>(buffer, 0, numElements / sizeof(GCGLushort));
3389 break;
3390 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
3391 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLuint>(buffer, 0, numElements / sizeof(GCGLuint));
3392 break;
3393 default:
3394 return false;
3395 }
3396 if (maxIndex)
3397 elementArrayBuffer->setCachedMaxIndex(type, maxIndex.value());
3398 }
3399
3400 if (!maxIndex)
3401 return false;
3402
3403 // The number of required elements is one more than the maximum
3404 // index that will be accessed.
3405 auto checkedNumElementsRequired = checkedAddAndMultiply<unsigned>(maxIndex.value(), 1, 1);
3406 if (!checkedNumElementsRequired)
3407 return false;
3408 numElementsRequired = checkedNumElementsRequired.value();
3409
3410 return true;
3411}

3438template<typename T, typename TypedArrayType>
3439std::optional<GCGLSpan<const T>> WebGL2RenderingContext::validateClearBuffer(const char* functionName, GCGLenum buffer, TypedList<TypedArrayType, T>& values, GCGLuint srcOffset)
3440{
3441 Checked<GCGLsizei, RecordOverflow> checkedSize(values.length());
3442 checkedSize -= srcOffset;
3443 if (checkedSize.hasOverflowed()) {
3444 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid array size / srcOffset");
3445 return { };
3446 }
3447 switch (buffer) {
3448 case GraphicsContextGL::COLOR:
3449 if (checkedSize < 4) {
3450 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid array size / srcOffset");
3451 return { };
3452 }
3453 return makeGCGLSpan(values.data() + srcOffset, 4);
3454 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH:
3455 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL:
3456 if (checkedSize < 1) {
3457 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid array size / srcOffset");
3458 return { };
3459 }
3460 return makeGCGLSpan(values.data() + srcOffset, 1);
3461
3462 default:
3463 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid buffer");
3464 return { };
3465 }
3466}

3657void WebGL2RenderingContext::updateBuffersToAutoClear(ClearBufferCaller caller, GCGLenum buffer, GCGLint drawbuffer)
3658{
3659 // This method makes sure that we don't auto-clear any buffers which the
3660 // user has manually cleared using the new ES 3.0 clearBuffer* APIs.
3661
3662 // If the user has a framebuffer bound, don't update the auto-clear
3663 // state of the built-in back buffer.
3664 if (m_framebufferBinding)
3665 return;
3666
3667 // If the scissor test is on, assume that we can't short-circuit
3668 // these clears.
3669 if (m_scissorEnabled)
3670 return;
3671
3672 // The default back buffer only has one color attachment.
3673 if (drawbuffer)
3674 return;
3675
3676 // If the call to the driver generated an error, don't claim that
3677 // we've auto-cleared these buffers. The early returns below are for
3678 // cases where errors will be produced.
3679
3680 // The default back buffer is currently always RGB(A)8, which
3681 // restricts the variants which can legally be used to clear the
3682 // color buffer. TODO(crbug.com/829632): this needs to be
3683 // generalized.
3684 switch (caller) {
3685 case ClearBufferCaller::ClearBufferiv:
3686 if (buffer != GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL)
3687 return;
3688 break;
3689 case ClearBufferCaller::ClearBufferfv:
3690 if (buffer != GraphicsContextGL::COLOR && buffer != GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH)
3691 return;
3692 break;
3693 case ClearBufferCaller::ClearBufferuiv:
3694 return;
3695 case ClearBufferCaller::ClearBufferfi:
3696 if (buffer != GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL)
3697 return;
3698 break;
3699 }
3700
3701 GCGLbitfield buffersToClear = 0;
3702
3703 // Turn it into a bitfield and mask it off.
3704 switch (buffer) {
3705 case GraphicsContextGL::COLOR:
3706 buffersToClear = GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
3707 break;
3708 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH:
3709 buffersToClear = GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT;
3710 break;
3711 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL:
3712 buffersToClear = GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
3713 break;
3714 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL:
3715 buffersToClear = GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT | GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
3716 break;
3717 default:
3718 // Illegal value.
3719 return;
3720 }
3721
3722 m_context->setBuffersToAutoClear(m_context->getBuffersToAutoClear() & (~buffersToClear));
3723}
